<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Consul General at Shanghai (
                        Josselyn
                    ) to the Secretary of
                            State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945v07</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d1108</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">1108</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-12-11T00:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-12-11T23:59:59-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-12-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-12-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="1108" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1108">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.61A/12–1145: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Josselyn</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-12-11">December 11,
                            1945</date>.<lb/>[Received December 11—11:01 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>354. Informed 40 members Ministry of Agriculture including Minister and/or Vice
                    Minister moving Nanking few days.</p>
                <p>Therefore important know Department’s views re proposal for agricultural
                    collaboration as soon as possible in order make plans for mission’s
                    accommodation at Nanking or elsewhere.</p>
                <p>Early advice from Department would be helpful. Sent to Department. Repeated to
                    Chungking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Josselyn</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
